OL,3,CTourists urged to avoid car hire
OL,4,Ccompany over 'serious issues'
OL,6,FRory Boland, editor of magazine Which?
OL,7,FTravel, said: "Booking car hire should
OL,8,Fbe straightforward, but all too often
OL,9,Fit feels like the wild west, with
OL,10,Ftravellers lamenting fraught
OL,11,Fexperiences, poor customer service and
OL,12,Fspurious fees.
OL,14,F"Goldcar in particular is best
OL,15,Favoided, with customers repeatedly
OL,16,Freporting serious issues from pressure
OL,17,Fselling to poor customer service.
OL,19,F"To ensure you have the best possible
OL,20,Fexperience this summer, make sure you
OL,21,Fbook with a reputable firm."
